24:26.424 --> 24:28.881
Welcome to New Orleans, y'all!

24:29.010 --> 24:30.500
— Hey!
— Lovely!

24:30.637 --> 24:32.753
— Yeah!
— Whoo!

24:34.140 --> 24:36.051
(Man) Police were drawn
to this housing project

24:36.184 --> 24:39.176
because a Mardi Gras Indian chief
cut through this fence behind me

24:39.312 --> 24:40.973
and occupied a unit over there.

24:41.105 --> 24:45.644
Now this Indian chief says he will not leave until these
apartments are reopened.

24:45.777 --> 24:47.938
— Earlier today, Albert Lambreaux...
- There you go.

24:48.071 --> 24:52.064
..a chief with one of the downtown
Indian tribes, had this to say.

24:52.200 --> 24:54.657
What sense does it make
for the government

24:54.786 --> 24:57.198
— to be sitting on all this housing...
- Yes, sir.

24:57.330 --> 25:00.288
— ..when so many people can't get home?
— That's right.

25:00.416 --> 25:02.623
(Albert) I need somebody to explain that to me.

25:02.752 --> 25:05.209
And now others
have taken up the protest as well,

25:05.338 --> 25:07.624
with squatters setting up
in two other buildings...

25:07.757 --> 25:10.624
— That's what I'm talking about.
— ..here at the BW Cooper project,

25:10.760 --> 25:14.173
and others, cutting a hole through the fence
of the St. Bernard complex

25:14.305 --> 25:16.591
and occupying two units over there.

25:16.724 --> 25:20.683
(Singing with CD) J‘ Shame, shame, shame
what you have done

25:22.021 --> 25:24.637
J‘ We was on the ropes,
we were down and out

25:24.774 --> 25:27.641
J‘ You flew on over, never did come down

25:27.777 --> 25:31.486
J‘ Shame, shame, shame
