25:32.949 --> 25:36.942
J‘ Shame, shame, shame
on you now, Dubya J‘

25:40.748 --> 25:42.784
(Davis) Oh, no.

25:57.849 --> 25:59.760
Cray?

26:08.109 --> 26:10.191
Creighton?

26:23.875 --> 26:24.955
(Toni sighs)

26:25.084 --> 26:28.702
You're working on the novel. That's great.

26:28.838 --> 26:31.375
What are you doing out here?
What's wrong with the study?

26:31.507 --> 26:33.043
(Groans)

26:33.176 --> 26:35.167
Have you eaten yet?
You wanna go out for a bite?

26:35.303 --> 26:36.964
Toni! Shh!

26:46.397 --> 26:48.353
(Man outside) Chief Lambreaux?

26:48.483 --> 26:50.064
(Knock at door)

26:50.193 --> 26:52.559
(People shouting outside)
Hell, no! We won't go!

26:53.821 --> 26:56.688
Let 'em know, Big Chief! Let 'em know!

26:58.743 --> 27:02.702
Chief Lambreaux,
you mind if I come in and talk?

27:02.830 --> 27:05.663
If you can find it in yourself
not to lock me up,

27:05.792 --> 27:09.159
I can find it in myself
to welcome you to my home.

27:09.295 --> 27:11.001
You have my word.

27:15.718 --> 27:19.256
(Man) Let's go, Chief! Chief's on that fiyo!

27:19.388 --> 27:22.255
Kind of a half—assed stand—off,
if you ask me.

27:22.391 --> 27:23.676
(Locks door)

27:23.810 --> 27:26.722
My people come and go as they please.

27:26.854 --> 27:29.266
We're not looking
to start anything here with y'all.

27:29.398 --> 27:30.934
Mm.

27:32.318 --> 27:34.309
You look disappointed.

27:35.905 --> 27:40.069
I'm Sergeant Maurice Thompson,
Community Relations Division.

27:40.201 --> 27:42.066
Community Relations?

27:42.203 --> 27:45.195
That's nice. How can I help you, Sergeant?

27:45.915 --> 27:49.123
Well, the mayor's office
and Council President Thomas,

27:49.252 --> 27:53.165
they sent me here to say they want
to resolve this without any real conflict.

27:53.297 --> 27:57.506
Well, that's easily done. Open the projects.

27:57.635 --> 28:00.798
Federal government's got control
of these projects.

28:00.930 --> 28:03.967
- You know this.
— Yeah, they keep saying.

28:04.100 --> 28:07.558
It don't make no sense
that nobody in New Orleans

28:07.687 --> 28:09.268
is fighting the feds on this one.

28:10.273 --> 28:12.264
What does that tell you?

28:13.192 --> 28:15.729
If people wanted
the housing projects to reopen...

28:15.862 --> 28:17.523
I mean if voters wanted it,

28:17.655 --> 28:21.694
you'd see the politicians
falling all over each other to demand it.

28:21.826 --> 28:23.737
But the people who vote in this town,

28:23.870 --> 28:26.452
black and white both,
they've been awfully quiet

28:26.581 --> 28:30.039
on this thing so far, don't you think?

28:30.167 --> 28:33.330
Now if you want to spend another night here
to drive your point home,

28:33.462 --> 28:35.714
we ain't gonna bother you.

28:35.840 --> 28:40.425
Come tomorrow afternoon, we're gonna
have to treat this as a criminal trespass.

28:41.637 --> 28:44.014
And you and anyone in here with you

28:44.140 --> 28:45.971
is going to jail.

28:50.980 --> 28:53.392
Well, thank you for your visit, Sergeant.

28:57.278 --> 28:59.564
And come again.

29:05.912 --> 29:09.496
(Woman over PA) Dr. Koch to the ER,
Dr. Koch to the ER.

29:26.766 --> 29:29.007
(PA) Paging Dr. Wasserman.

29:29.143 --> 29:31.179
(Playing along with recording)

29:44.533 --> 29:46.694
(Fast—fonNarding)

30:06.722 --> 30:08.508
(Toni) Hi.

30:08.641 --> 30:10.848
Coffee.

30:10.977 --> 30:12.387
Set it down.

30:12.520 --> 30:14.602
Oh, you got some pages done.

30:14.730 --> 30:16.891
— They're shit.
- Can I read?

30:17.024 --> 30:19.982
Why would you want to read it
if I just told you they were shit?

30:20.903 --> 30:24.020
What the fuck am I doing here anyway?

30:24.156 --> 30:25.862
I don't even know.

30:25.992 --> 30:28.574
Maybe you want to leave this alone
until after Mardi Gras.

30:28.703 --> 30:31.945
— Will I be 20 years younger after Mardi Gras?
— What?

30:32.081 --> 30:35.699
Toni, just let me do my work,
will you, please?

30:44.135 --> 30:46.091
(Man speaking French)

30:51.100 --> 30:53.341
Mademoiselle.

30:54.395 --> 30:56.932
I made your favorite. Crab bisque.

30:58.649 --> 31:00.355
You are sweet.

31:00.484 --> 31:02.395
This is my neighbor Souleymane.

31:02.528 --> 31:04.314
— Chef Janette.
— How are you, Chef?

31:04.447 --> 31:06.438
— Nice to meet you.
— Nice to meet you.

31:06.574 --> 31:08.815
This is your new kitchen!

31:08.951 --> 31:12.819
Yeah. No staff, no silvenNare.
Just me and my propane.

31:12.955 --> 31:14.536
Wow. (Laughs)

31:14.665 --> 31:17.407
(Laughs) I'm gonna be at Bacchanal
this weekend.

31:17.543 --> 31:20.000
I could use a hand,
if you want to have an adventure.

31:20.129 --> 31:24.247
Very kind of you to offer,
but I'm working the grill at Bayona.

31:24.383 --> 31:26.669
— Oh, Jacques, that's great.
- Yeah.

31:26.802 --> 31:29.635
Oh, I knew you'd get snapped up.

31:29.764 --> 31:31.300
Well, it won't be the same.

31:31.432 --> 31:33.844
You know they'll probably
pay you more than I could afford.

31:33.976 --> 31:36.718
— You'll be making what you're worth.
— But not the same.

31:36.854 --> 31:38.310
Yeah.

31:41.317 --> 31:44.184
Here's a copy of the order
signed by Judge Gatling.

31:45.821 --> 31:47.937
Well, your timing's pretty good anyway.

31:48.074 --> 31:50.360
The state just completed this
a few weeks back.

31:50.493 --> 31:54.406
Every Orleans Parish prisoner
currently housed outside the parish.

31:54.538 --> 31:56.324
Photographs and fingerprints.

31:56.457 --> 31:59.369
— Every one?
- 527 total.

31:59.502 --> 32:01.458
We need to look at every face.

32:01.587 --> 32:05.876
I need you to fill out this form indicating that you won't
disclose any confidential information

32:06.008 --> 32:08.124
except as a means of locating Mr. Brooks.

32:08.260 --> 32:12.424
You can tell the sheriff
his ass is fully covered.

32:12.556 --> 32:14.842
Hope you find him, ma'am. I truly mean that.

32:14.975 --> 32:17.182
Thank you, Deputy.

32:18.562 --> 32:21.144
Let's do this. Let's get it done.

32:25.152 --> 32:28.144
— (Phone ringing)
— (Radio) One—nine. Ten—four.

32:37.289 --> 32:40.201
Ten—four. Two—fifty. We have...

32:49.176 --> 32:50.507
Davis McAlary.

32:50.636 --> 32:52.217
Judge Williams.

32:52.346 --> 32:53.927
I am indeed.

32:54.056 --> 32:57.344
Wow, summoned to lunch
by a New Orleans judge.

32:57.476 --> 33:01.014
— I'm a fan. I hope you'll sign that for me.
- No problem.

33:01.147 --> 33:03.433
You've been having fun
the last few weeks, Davis.

33:03.566 --> 33:07.104
That business of Greased Palm Sunday.

33:07.236 --> 33:10.774
Of course not everyone thinks
of the election as a joke.

33:10.906 --> 33:12.362
I don't think it's a joke.

33:12.491 --> 33:13.776
(Laughs)

33:13.909 --> 33:15.740
How long have you lived in New Orleans?

33:15.870 --> 33:17.701
You've sold some CDs.

33:17.830 --> 33:20.037
Now, don't you think it's time to stand down,

33:20.166 --> 33:25.456
let the people of District C focus
on the serious choice they have to make?

33:25.588 --> 33:27.249
Oh, it's on me.

33:28.257 --> 33:31.966
Uh, trout Baquet, a side of red beans
and a Budweiser.

33:32.094 --> 33:34.210
The gumbo for me, with iced tea.

33:34.346 --> 33:36.257
Wait, Judge, I'm confused.

33:36.390 --> 33:38.301
Why exactly are you buying me lunch?

33:38.434 --> 33:41.642
Because, Davis,
it's a horse race in District C,

33:41.770 --> 33:43.977
and you're siphoning votes
from the candidate

33:44.106 --> 33:46.267
that our organization is supporting.

33:46.400 --> 33:48.766
Whose poll shows that?

33:49.778 --> 33:51.279
Jeez.

33:52.948 --> 33:55.030
What? 4.3%?

33:55.159 --> 33:57.992
Most of which comes
at the expense of our man.

33:58.120 --> 33:59.235
Which is who?

33:59.371 --> 34:01.578
Your little musicale

34:01.707 --> 34:05.165
can mean the difference
between him being in the runoff or not.

34:05.294 --> 34:09.458
So I am here to offer you something.

34:09.590 --> 34:11.251
A bribe?

34:11.383 --> 34:13.248
Sweet!

34:13.385 --> 34:14.921
You know what that is?

34:15.054 --> 34:17.966
— A business card.
— No, Davis.

34:18.098 --> 34:21.511
That is a "get out ofjail free" card.

34:21.644 --> 34:24.010
Next time you find yourself in trouble,

34:24.146 --> 34:27.263
and you being a musician,
we know there's always a next time,

34:27.399 --> 34:29.355
you call Judge Williams.

34:29.485 --> 34:31.225
That's my cell number on the back.

34:33.864 --> 34:36.196
Wait, so you're saying

34:36.325 --> 34:38.611
if...if I quit the city council race...

34:38.744 --> 34:41.076
Then you have a new friend.

34:44.541 --> 34:47.032
Do we have a deal?

34:50.381 --> 34:51.837
Yes.

34:52.883 --> 34:57.217
(Violin playing, tuning)

34:57.346 --> 34:59.382
What's up, y'all?

34:59.515 --> 35:01.471
Thanks for giving me a shot, guys.

35:01.600 --> 35:06.060
Oh, no problem. Harley there said you're pretty good at that
country stuff. So let's jam.

35:06.188 --> 35:07.974
He's being kind.

35:08.107 --> 35:11.099
Well, Cedric's my number—one call
when it comes to Pine Leaf gigs,

35:11.235 --> 35:14.727
but from time to time he's out with
Eddie Poullard and we need a sub.

35:14.863 --> 35:16.728
And being a girl ain't gonna hurt nothing.

35:16.865 --> 35:20.073
Well, I hope I can do itjustice.

35:20.911 --> 35:24.699
Well, how about we try Homage A Poullard?

35:24.832 --> 35:26.368
All right, let's do it.

35:26.500 --> 35:29.367
(Accordion playing, drum thumping)

35:57.781 --> 36:00.158
(Playing goes out of time)

36:04.788 --> 36:07.120
I think I'm missing the one.

36:07.249 --> 36:09.285
- I'm sorry.
— It's a little tricky.

36:09.418 --> 36:11.750
Yeah, I'll show you where to come in. Watch.

36:21.722 --> 36:23.007
(Man) Whoo!

36:28.020 --> 36:29.851
(Playing out of time)

36:41.867 --> 36:45.109
I'm sorry, guys. I'm playing terrible.

36:45.245 --> 36:48.658
It's not about the notes.
It's about the feeling of the music.

36:48.791 --> 36:51.282
I know I can play better than this.

36:52.961 --> 36:55.293
I'm just guessing now, but...

36:55.422 --> 36:58.038
you have trouble in your heart?

36:58.175 --> 37:00.416
Yeah, a little bit.

37:00.552 --> 37:04.340
Well, why don't you get it together
and we'll hear you another time?

37:04.473 --> 37:05.804
Yeah.

37:05.933 --> 37:08.800
Don't worry about it.
Don't even worry about it.

37:11.480 --> 37:14.847
— (Radio chatter)
— This can't be all of them.

37:14.983 --> 37:18.601
If Daymo was in custody,
his photo would be here

37:18.737 --> 37:20.648
under any name in any parish.

37:20.781 --> 37:22.066
We would have seen his photo.

37:22.199 --> 37:25.032
So where is he, then?
Are they hiding him from us?

37:25.160 --> 37:27.993
No, they don't want a judge
to hold them in contempt.

37:28.122 --> 37:29.987
Then what?

37:35.504 --> 37:37.711
If he'd been released...

37:37.840 --> 37:41.753
He would have come home.
He would have called Mama.

37:52.396 --> 37:55.763
Deputy, is there a master list
of OPP inmates

37:55.899 --> 37:58.356
who died in custody since Katrina?

37:58.485 --> 37:59.986
I can get it.

38:00.112 --> 38:02.444
Might take me a little time,
but I can get it for you.

38:02.573 --> 38:04.564
Please.

38:11.623 --> 38:14.865
(Crowd chanting) We deserve a home!
We deserve a home!

38:15.002 --> 38:17.664
(Franklin) They getting ready
to do something.

38:17.796 --> 38:19.502
(Albert) Mm.

38:20.632 --> 38:22.133
Y'all fellas got to leave.

38:22.259 --> 38:25.877
— Nobody leaving.
— We got what we came here for.

38:26.013 --> 38:29.221
It's time for me to do that jail walk
and drive the point home.

38:32.060 --> 38:33.971
Just go home. Keep sewing.

38:34.104 --> 38:36.846
Mardi Gras won't wait.

38:36.982 --> 38:40.224
And be there with my bail money tomorrow.

38:40.360 --> 38:42.066
A'ight?

38:42.196 --> 38:44.608
(Crowd) We deserve a home!
We deserve a home!

38:44.740 --> 38:46.731
(Chanting continues)

38:49.077 --> 38:52.490
We deserve a home!
We deserve a home!

38:54.750 --> 38:58.584
Apparently, the original protester,
Albert Lambreaux...

38:58.712 --> 39:00.577
(Man) Y'all weren't doing nothing wrong.
Go back in there!

39:00.714 --> 39:02.670
(Crowd booing)

39:04.218 --> 39:06.209
Fuck the police!

39:12.809 --> 39:15.346
(Angry shouting)

39:23.612 --> 39:25.273
(Man) It's time to end this!

39:25.405 --> 39:27.532
Will you vacate
or do we have to take the door down?

39:27.658 --> 39:29.444
(Albert) It's unlocked.

39:29.576 --> 39:31.077
Will you step outside?

39:31.203 --> 39:33.990
- (Generator off)
— No, sir, Iwill not.

39:39.920 --> 39:42.707
Down on your knees, hands on your head.
You're under arrest.

39:43.549 --> 39:46.882
On your knees, hands on your head.
You're under arrest.

39:47.010 --> 39:50.673
I won't kneel down.
You want to handcuff me? Go ahead.

39:50.806 --> 39:52.842
Motherfucker, you don't decide
how you go to jail.

39:52.975 --> 39:56.433
We decide how you go to jail.
On your fucking knees.

39:56.562 --> 39:59.269
— No hoom—bow.
— (Man) Oh, yeah.

39:59.398 --> 40:01.389
Fuck that Injun shit.

40:08.532 --> 40:11.695
Stop resisting! Stop resisting!

40:12.703 --> 40:14.910
Stay down! Stay down!

40:15.038 --> 40:16.539
He won't be here under his own name.

40:16.665 --> 40:19.407
I've checked with DMORT
every week since the storm.

40:19.543 --> 40:20.874
So how we gonna know, then?

40:21.003 --> 40:24.370
He might be a John Doe
or under a different name. I don't know.

40:24.506 --> 40:26.497
You ready to do this?

40:37.686 --> 40:39.517
That's my cousin's name.

40:45.277 --> 40:46.983
Jerome Cherry.

40:47.112 --> 40:49.854
And he ain't dead.
I seen him over Christmas.

40:51.700 --> 40:54.191
LaDonna, has Daymo
ever used your cousin's name?

40:54.328 --> 40:55.283
What?

40:55.412 --> 40:57.323
What if Daymo said he was Jerome Cherry?

40:57.456 --> 40:58.616
Why would he do that?

40:58.749 --> 41:01.536
Maybe he thought taking another name
would get him released,

41:01.668 --> 41:03.624
like Keevon White did to him.

41:03.754 --> 41:06.746
Your cousin Jerome has never been
in trouble with the law, I bet.

41:08.008 --> 41:09.839
Boy was damn near raised in a church.

41:09.968 --> 41:13.426
You see? Daymo got locked up
because there was a bench warrant

41:13.555 --> 41:15.466
on David Maurice Brooks.

41:15.599 --> 41:17.555
After he lost his wristband,

41:17.684 --> 41:19.675
maybe he gave himself another name,

41:19.811 --> 41:22.723
one with no criminal record.

41:25.275 --> 41:29.439
That says, "Family notified.
Body unclaimed."

41:29.571 --> 41:31.232
Mm—hm.

41:31.365 --> 41:33.321
What family?

41:33.450 --> 41:35.156
Who'd they notify?

41:36.203 --> 41:38.569
I don't understand what the fuck's going on.

41:38.705 --> 41:43.074
They got my brother's body somewhere
under somebody else's name?

41:43.210 --> 41:45.121
We can't know for sure.

41:45.253 --> 41:47.790
We'll drive over to DMORT tomorrow.

41:47.923 --> 41:50.005
In St. Gabriel?

41:50.133 --> 41:52.124
No, they moved it to Carville,

41:52.260 --> 41:54.546
70 miles west of us.

41:54.680 --> 41:56.921
LaDonna?

41:57.933 --> 42:00.640
We're gonna have to look at this body.

42:07.984 --> 42:09.815
(Knocking)

42:09.945 --> 42:11.856
(Janette) Coming.

42:11.988 --> 42:13.944
Hold on.

42:20.372 --> 42:22.613
I cooked for you.

42:22.749 --> 42:26.958
Stuffed mirlitons, spinach salad
and a bottle of Malbec.

42:28.004 --> 42:29.790
You went by the restaurant, huh?

42:30.507 --> 42:32.088
Why didn't you tell me?

42:32.217 --> 42:34.208
What is there to say?

42:35.387 --> 42:37.673
Janette, I'm sorry.

42:37.806 --> 42:41.344
Yeah, no more free meals at the bar.

42:42.602 --> 42:44.558
I'm sorry for you, darlin'.

43:01.997 --> 43:04.238
Christ. (Laughs)

43:04.374 --> 43:07.036
Oh, yeah, still no electric down here,

43:07.169 --> 43:10.002
no drywall, nobody doing any work on it at all.

43:10.756 --> 43:14.248
I guess I should be embarrassed,
living like this.

43:14.384 --> 43:16.841
I'm not company, Janette. I'm your friend.

43:17.846 --> 43:19.427
With benefits.

43:19.556 --> 43:21.763
With or without.

43:25.020 --> 43:26.851
Come on.

43:26.980 --> 43:28.936
We can eat upstairs.

43:31.109 --> 43:32.940
(Printer whirring)

43:38.200 --> 43:39.781
OK.

43:44.206 --> 43:45.992
Ahem.

43:48.210 --> 43:50.417
Creighton Bernette here,
still in New Orleans,

43:50.545 --> 43:52.536
which is still where you left it.

43:53.215 --> 43:56.207
I'm sorry if I'm making a pest of myself here.

43:56.343 --> 43:59.085
I would hate to exacerbate
any growing sense

43:59.221 --> 44:02.054
of "Katrina fatigue" in the country at large.

44:02.182 --> 44:05.015
Perhaps you've experienced
this "Katrina fatigue"

44:05.143 --> 44:08.385
if you watch TV
or read your hometown paper.

44:08.522 --> 44:13.562
I mean, it was fun for a while
being outraged at the national response.

44:13.693 --> 44:17.402
And the pictures from the Dome
and the Convention Center were shocking.

44:18.031 --> 44:20.647
Anderson Cooper was here.

44:20.784 --> 44:23.526
Katie Couric too.

44:23.662 --> 44:27.746
But now we're on our own.

44:27.874 --> 44:29.990
And here's the thing.

44:30.126 --> 44:34.415
For a while, I thought we could rely
on our sense of ourselves,

44:34.548 --> 44:38.962
on the fact that we were,
regardless of race, class or color,

44:39.094 --> 44:41.676
New Orleanians first and last.

44:41.805 --> 44:45.764
But there's an election coming, right?

44:45.892 --> 44:48.133
And no way a shared sense of purpose

44:48.270 --> 44:51.228
is gonna survive a New Orleans election.

44:51.356 --> 44:53.472
Right?

44:53.608 --> 44:56.850
Now there are people
openly delighted with the fact

44:56.987 --> 45:01.026
that thousands of exiles,
most of them black, won't be able to vote.

45:01.157 --> 45:05.617
Meanwhile our incumbent mayor,
sensing this,

45:05.745 --> 45:10.159
talks crudely about New Orleans
remaining a "chocolate city."

45:10.292 --> 45:12.999
